## 📦 Requirements

Django==4.2
Pillow==10.0.0
django-crispy-forms==2.0
crispy-bootstrap5==0.7

csharp
Copier le code

Install with:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
⚙️ Configuration Highlights (settings.py)
Static files:
STATICFILES_DIRS = [BASE_DIR / 'static']

Media files:
MEDIA_URL = '/media/'
MEDIA_ROOT = BASE_DIR / 'media'

Templates:
DIRS = [BASE_DIR / 'templates']

Authentication Redirects:

LOGIN_URL = 'login'

LOGIN_REDIRECT_URL = '/'

LOGOUT_REDIRECT_URL = '/'

Crispy Forms:
Using bootstrap5 as the template pack.

🚀 Features
🔐 User registration, login/logout

🎨 Upload and display artworks with categories and styles

💬 Commenting system with timestamps

❤️ Like/unlike functionality using AJAX

📈 Artwork view counting

📷 Image resizing and optimization with Pillow

🔍 Search, filter, and sort (by popularity, views, latest)

🧑 User profiles with avatar and bio

🧾 Pagination for browsing artworks

🌟 Admin dashboard with management features

📱 Responsive templates using Bootstrap 5

🧪 Setup Instructions
1. Clone and Navigate
bash
Copier le code
git clone <repo-url>
cd art_gallery
2. Create a virtual environment
bash
Copier le code
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate  # Windows
# or
source venv/bin/activate  # macOS/Linux
3. Install dependencies
bash
Copier le code
pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Migrate and create superuser
bash
Copier le code
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser
5. Run development server
bash
Copier le code
python manage.py runserver
Then go to:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/

🧩 Admin Setup Tips
Log in to /admin/ and add some categories:

Abstract Art

Digital Art

Photography

Generative Art

Mixed Media

🖼️ Screens & Pages
/ – Homepage with filters, featured artworks, pagination

/artwork/<id>/ – Artwork detail view

/upload/ – Upload a new artwork

/profile/ – View & edit your own profile

/profile/<username>/ – View others' profiles

/accounts/login/ – Login

/register/ – Registration page

🛠️ Folder Setup Commands (optional)
If you need to manually create folders:

cmd
Copier le code
mkdir templates
mkdir templates\gallery
mkdir templates\registration

mkdir static
mkdir static\css
mkdir static\js
mkdir static\images

mkdir media
mkdir media\artworks
mkdir media\avatars
Or use PowerShell:

powershell
Copier le code
mkdir templates/gallery, templates/registration
mkdir static/css, static/js, static/images
mkdir media/artworks, media/avatars
📸 Gallery Model Summary
Artwork: title, description, category, style, image, views, featured, artist

Category: for grouping artworks

Like: connects users to liked artworks

Comment: user-generated feedback

UserProfile: extended user info (bio, avatar, etc.)

